📘 Data Dictionary – Gold Layer (Data Warehouse)

🌟 Overview

The Gold Layer represents the final, business-ready data model structured using a Star Schema. It contains:

Dimension Tables: Customers, Products
Fact Table: Sales

This layer is optimized for analytics, reporting, and BI tools like Power BI.

1.👤 Gold_Dim_Customers – Customer Dimension

| Column Name     | Data Type | Description                              |
| --------------- | --------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Customer_Key    | INT       | Surrogate key generated using ROW_NUMBER |
| Customer_Id     | INT       | Unique customer ID from CRM system       |
| Customer_Number | VARCHAR   | Business key for customer                |
| First_Name      | VARCHAR   | Customer first name                      |
| Last_Name       | VARCHAR   | Customer last name                       |
| Country         | VARCHAR   | Customer country from location table     |
| Martial_Status  | VARCHAR   | Marital status of customer               |
| Gender          | VARCHAR   | Gender (CRM preferred, fallback to ERP)  |
| Birthdate       | DATE      | Customer birth date                      |
| Cst_Create_Date | DATE      | Record creation date                     |

🧠 Notes
CRM is treated as the primary source for Gender
COALESCE ensures no null values
Combines data from CRM + ERP systems

2. 📦 Gold_Dim_Products – Product Dimension
  
📌 Description

Contains product-related information including category hierarchy.

| Column Name    | Data Type | Description                 |
| -------------- | --------- | --------------------------- |
| Product_Key    | INT       | Surrogate key               |
| Product_ID     | INT       | Product ID                  |
| Product_Number | VARCHAR   | Unique product code         |
| Product_Name   | VARCHAR   | Name of the product         |
| Category_ID    | INT       | Category identifier         |
| Category       | VARCHAR   | Product category            |
| SubCategory    | VARCHAR   | Product subcategory         |
| Maintainence   | VARCHAR   | Maintenance type            |
| Cost           | DECIMAL   | Product cost                |
| Product_Line   | VARCHAR   | Product line classification |
| Start_Date     | DATE      | Product active start date   |

🧠 Notes
Filters only current products (Prd_End_Dt IS NULL)
Supports hierarchical analysis (Category → SubCategory)

3. 💰 Gold_Fact_Sales – Sales Fact Table

📌 Description

Stores transactional sales data. Acts as the central table connecting dimensions.

| Column Name   | Data Type | Description                      |
| ------------- | --------- | -------------------------------- |
| Order_Number  | VARCHAR   | Unique sales order number        |
| Product_Key   | INT       | Foreign key → Product dimension  |
| Customer_Key  | INT       | Foreign key → Customer dimension |
| Order_Date    | DATE      | Date of order                    |
| Shipping_Date | DATE      | Date of shipment                 |
| Due_Date      | DATE      | Delivery due date                |
| Sales_Amount  | DECIMAL   | Total sales amount               |
| Quantity      | INT       | Number of items sold             |
| Price         | DECIMAL   | Price per unit                   |


🧠 Notes
This is the central fact table
Enables:
Sales trend analysis 📈
Customer purchase behavior 👤
Product performance 📦

🔗 Relationships (Star Schema)

Gold_Fact_Sales.Customer_Key → Gold_Dim_Customers.Customer_Key
Gold_Fact_Sales.Product_Key → Gold_Dim_Products.Product_Key
